COMMANDER KEEN WINS AT THE FIRST ANNUAL SHAREWARE INDUSTRY AWARDS!

Apogee is proud to announce that the Commander Keen series won two major
categoies at the shareware industry's first annual awards ceremony.

1) Best Entertainment
2) Best Overall

In the Best Entertainment category Commander Keen's primary competition was
from another top Apogee game, Duke Nukum.

Winning the Best Overall category (equivalent to the Oscar's Best Picture) was
a major accomplishment.  Commander Keen was up against major nominations such
as As-Easy-As (a Lotus 1-2-3 style spreadsheet), 4DOS (a COMMAND.COM
replacement that is also available as NDOS in the new Norton Utilities
package), and A86 (a brilliantly implemented assembler).

Even more impressive is the fact that since this was the first ever Shareware
Industry Awards ceremony, it represented everything released in the past ten
years existance of shareware.  Next year's awards will only represent the
previous year.


We thank you for your interest and patronage,

Scott Miller, President
George Broussard, Executive Vice President
Steven Blackburn, Vice President, Operations


