              $15 per episode, or $30 for all three episodes!

In the not-so-distant future the calamity of World War III led to eventual
world peace.  But it did not last...

Earth was invaded by alien marauders--the Kretons.  Earth's united military
force, still depleted after the mighty onslaught of WWIII, was not nearly
sufficient to repel the numerous Kreton attacks.

It was discovered that the Kretons had used a wormhole to invade our region
of space from their home worlds.  And with that knowledge Earth called into
action Major Harrison Stryker, hero of WWIII, to travel back through the
worm hole and destroy the Kreton's home world headquarters.

With almost no chance of success, you accept the mission...

Major Stryker is the first Apogee game with "triple-parallax scrolling",
adding to the illusion of depth and danger.  Your mission is to pilot a
high-powered, armored space ship through dozens of stunning scenerios, such
as space stations, lava caves and alien cities.

Exciting features:
  Ad Lib music and Sound Blaster digitized effects.
  EGA/VGA high-speed animated graphics.
  Cinematic sequences.
  Unlike any other Apogee game yet.
  Full of bonuses and secrets to discover.
  Save and restore up to 10 games.
  Play with joystick or keyboard.
  Exciting demo mode.

If you're into action-filled, heart pounding shoot 'em ups, then Major Stryker
is your ticket to adventure.

HOW TO ORDER:
There are three unique episodes of Major Stryker, all building upon the main
story.  Each episode is $15, or you can order (and register) all three episodes
for only $30.  As an incentive to order all three, you'll also get the hints
sheet, the cheat codes, and a new bonus game from Apogee.  Plus, you can call
the Apogee hints line for assistance.  To order, call 1-800-GAME123.


